---

## Examples That Must Not Activate

The following must NOT activate the harness planning skill set:

- "What does this function do?" → do NOT activate (explanation)
- "Run the tests" → do NOT activate (direct command)
- "Fix the typo in line 42" → do NOT activate (trivial single-location change)
- "Rename this variable from x to y" → do NOT activate (trivial rename, no planning needed)
- "Explain how this API works" → do NOT activate (explanation)
- "Execute this accepted worker packet" → do NOT activate (route to `02-harness-execution.mdc`)
- "Can you help me write hello world?" → do NOT activate (trivial)
- "That's the plan — let's do it" → do NOT activate (execution intent, not planning intent; 'plan' is lexical false positive)
- "That's the plan — implement it now" → do NOT activate (execution directive even though 'plan' appears)
- "The plan looks good, proceed" → do NOT activate (execution approval)
- "looks good, go ahead" → do NOT activate (execution approval)
- "Run the approved worker packet" → do NOT activate (direct execution)
- Casual conversational questions → do NOT activate

